      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why M-Words Score Well in Scrabble</h2>
      <p>M's 3-point face value puts it above most vowels and common consonants (S, T, N, R are all 1 point). That means every M-word starts with a small advantage built in. When you combine M with power letters — X for MIX (12 points), Z for MAZY (18 points), or double Z for MUZZY (28 points) — the scores become exceptional for their word length.</p>
      <p>M also works beautifully in medium-length words that are common enough to recall under time pressure. MYSTIFY, MIXTURE, and MONKEY are all everyday words that deliver strong point totals. You don't need to memorise obscure words to score well with M — just know which combinations produce the best returns.</p>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Playing M-Words</h2>
      <p>M rewards players who understand its partnerships. Here are the key strategies for maximising M-word scores:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>M + X is your bread and butter:</strong> MIX, MAX, and MOX all score 12 points for just 3 letters. These short words fit almost anywhere and are devastating on premium squares.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>M + Z creates power words:</strong> MAZY (18 points), MUZZY (28 points), MUZZLE (26 points), and MIZZLE (26 points) are all extraordinarily high-value plays. Hold M when Z is available.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Use M as a hook:</strong> M hooks onto many existing words. IS → MIST, ATE → MATE, END → MEND. Front-hooking with M creates scoring opportunities without needing open board space.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>MY- words for Y disposal:</strong> When you're stuck with Y, M+Y combinations like MYTH (12 points), MYRRH (13 points), and MYSTIFY (18 points) help clear that tricky letter profitably.</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>Don't overlook MU- words:</strong> MUZZY, MUZZLE, MURKY, MUSHY, MUGGY — the MU- pattern is surprisingly productive for scoring plays.</span></li>
      </ul>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Essential M-Word Patterns</h2>
      <p>These M-word families are worth remembering for quick recall during competitive play:</p>
      <ul class="not-prose space-y-2 my-4">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>MI- words:</strong> MIX, MIXED, MIXER, MINX, MIXTURE — the MI prefix with X creates a whole family of high-scoring plays</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>MU- words:</strong> MUZZY, MUZZLE, MURKY, MUCKY, MUGGY — pair M with U and a strong consonant for consistent scoring</span></li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2 text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-blue-500 mt-0.5 shrink-0">▶</span><span><strong>MY- words:</strong> MYTH, MYRRH, MYSTIFY, MYSTIQUE, MYTHIC — the MY combination leverages Y's 4-point value naturally</span></li>
      </ul>

